                        <p>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>

            <p>
            </p>
        </li>

        <li>
                <definition xml:id="def-winning-coalition">
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                          A winning coalition is … coalition!winning  
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                </definition>
            <solution>
                <p>
                  one that has enough votes to win.
                A single player coalition can be a winning coalition only when that player is a dictator, so under the assumption that there are no dictators in our weighted voting system (dictators are boring) a winning coalition must have at least two players.  
                </p>
            </solution>

            <p>
            </p>

            <p>
                1
            </p>

            <p>
            </p>
        </li>

